Her mother is concerned that Jhonaiah does not fully understand her real potential. “We have a mother who did not go to school but who works hard and helps out at home. We have three children at school at present, but their sister, Jhonaiah, did well in test runs this year and she should try and accept to go back to school as soon as possible or even for next year,” Patricia said.

Just hours before news broke of the fatal accident involving 41-year-old Marvin Arthur of Canaries, St. John, his five-year-old daughter almost perished after a scorpion stung her eye, causing it to swell rapidly. In an interview with Observer Media, Marvin’s spouse, Natasha Arthur said she and Marvin’s five-year-old child were sleeping. However; while asleep, the little girl began feeling a lot of pain. Natasha sense something was wrong and became nervous.She placed an alarmed call to a local doctor but also carried out research about the sting online. The five-year-old was taken urgently to Victoria Hospital but after being assessed by doctors; they could not help.
